text:
the girl who lost her star

my heart broke as i wrote.

in her fatherâ€™s eyes she found delight
she lived to make him proud
to catch his gaze led to a plight
the moment he couldnâ€™t be found
she was his girl, he was her star
but suddenly everything changed
a vicious call heard in a car
the poor child looked deranged
â€œthe precious man you hold so dear
has now been placed in jailâ€
dissolved into a pool of tears
and hopelessness prevailed
now in her teens and lost it seems
no value for her life
no schools, no baths or brushing teeth
her days are filled with strife
her father writhes in pain so deep
he says itâ€™s all his fault
for promises he could not keep
canâ€™t love her from a vault
she has no love for anyone 
not even for herself
save for a boy whoâ€™s less than scum
who makes her feel bereft
days are consumed with stalking him
it really breaks my heart
her tiny eyes are now so dim
eâ€™er since she lost her star

text:
with the #metoo movement, we're in the era of calling people on their shit. here's my contribution..these are screenshots of messages i've received from my ex some time ago. the man that seemed to be the most enamored by me, was the biggest monster i've ever met.

#rkelly is the amplified model of what abuse looks like, but the color of a toxic relationship comes in many shades. so much so, that the simple solution of just leaving isn't as simple as it seems. and when you do walk away, there are psychological stains that come with it. this effect isn't just real for young girls, it's also real for grown, respected women who have their life together. 
i ask that you go through the images of messages and read over my personal list of warning signs.then share this message with a woman that you love and feel free to add to the list of warning signs.

bottom line..if you've been lucky to never experience abuse in your childhood, you don't easily recognize it until it's too late. you don't even know how to express what's happening to ask for help. you mistake it for the relationship going sour. but i have the tombstones of friends to back up my testimony and i'd rather speak my truth, than to add to that body of evidence. 
with all the friends that i have, i can count on 2 fingers, the number of people that helped me get away, 3 fingers of people who listened in support, but more fingers than i have to count, of people who watched and did nothing, defended him or added to the chaos-even blaming me. just like the reactions that have been seen in the case of the r. kelly situation. 
i hope that #rkelly gets the help that he needs, but wearing shackles while doing so. there's a difference between having a fetish and having a fetish that destroys the spirit of others. ğŸ¶the remix to ignition should put your ass in prisonğŸ¶

thank you to all the women that bared their soul for the documentary #survivingrkelly including one of my idolsÂ  @officialdreakelly. i hope this lightens your spirit so that you can soar like the eagles that you are. (and to fully understand the eagle reference,Â  google "rebirth of the eagle.")
@stopviolenceagainstwomen @metoomvmt @lifetimetv

text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. ***
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (linktree in bio to sign up) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
{bubbles < $ therapy}
letâ€™s talk about being apologetic, fickle, and silent in our intent and actions as women. why are we constantly apologizing for existing? how many times in a day do you apologize?
i was raised by a single mother and on a few occasions we were homeless. we stayed on peopleâ€™s floors or couches and each time we would wake up fairly early and make the space we slept in look as if we had never been there. i learned eventually to be silent in spaces. i rarely spoke up with my thoughts and feelings. i let many things slide and in any relationship i hardly ever said out loud if something bothered me. i was extremely passive and as a result iâ€™ve had nearly 30 years of some pretty shitty relationships.
iâ€™ve learned the hard way to stand up for myself and to not be silent as a woman and as a human being. it has not been mentally or physically healthy for me.
after trump won the election in 2016 i decided i would no longer put up with â€œbullshitâ€ and i would no longer be silent about things that deserved to be spoken about. i also go to therapy once a week and am working hard on gaining confidence in every area of my life.
this post is my reminder to everyone out there, that itâ€™s okay to not be silent, to be unapologetic, and to stand firm in decisions that are best for you or your loved ones. thatâ€™s okay. thatâ€™s healthy. â¤ï¸

text:
the words glow in the dark were written on my heart in the first few days of receiving divorce papers. â€¢

i had a flood of emotions, and had questions of â€œwhy me.â€ â€œwhy god didnâ€™t save this.â€ â€¢

yet amongst my tears, sleepless nights, and prayers, the words reigned loud and clear in my heart, glow in the dark. â€¢
it truthfully made no sense.  i had no idea how i could even do that , â€œglowâ€ amongst my deepest sorry and hurt. 
like,  for real, what god!? â€¢

however, when i came to the end of myself, gods strength began to rise up, and quickly i found the light and glow, god was talking about. â€¢

the enemy would love to keep you down. keep you in the dark, feeling defeated, lonely, abandon, unloved, unworthy. â€¢

but if you refuse to believe these lies, you will find that god is just getting started! â€¢

you 100% can be the light amongst the darkness, as you seek jesus! â€¢

if the enemy can keep you stuck, far from god  and only looking at the darkness that surrounds you, then god canâ€™t shine through you, and  finish your story. â€¢

and god wants you to radiate, no matter the dark place you may be in! â€¢
i donâ€™t know what you are going through today, - divorce - separation - loneliness - abuse - broken relationships - financial struggles - abandonment - loss of a loved one â€¢

i donâ€™t know. â€¢

but what i do know is, that you still have the ability to shine for jesus! â€¢

in fact, you can shine brighter and more beautiful than ever before. â€¢

light can shine brighter through a cracked vessel. the spaces allow for light to shine through in new ways and new designs.
â€¢

fill yourself with hope in jesus and as you seek him, through the broken cracks of your heart, his light will seep through you. â€¢
relentlessly pursue him, no matter how hopeless your situation may be! 
he will fill you with his light, and friend, you will 
glow in the dark âœ¨â€¢

text:
one of my cousins mentioned to watch the docuseries surviving r kelly. i was hesitant knowing what could arise but went ahead with my husband by my side. 
furious, unsettled, confused, so many negative emotions surfaced.

however, i admired the strength, bravery and courage these women displayed in breaking their silence. 
i am for no one to pass judgment on victims because until you experience it, you wonâ€™t understand what these victims go through.

after twisting and turning in bed for most of this morning my vision became clear for #2019. in breaking the silence: iâ€™m a survivor of child molestation in my grade school age, early teen years and sexual assault in the workplace as a young adult.  this year i start my journey to healing, breaking these generational curses and help to bring awareness to protect our little girls from these pedophiles out here.

text:
dear black women, 
you are worth more than the world can offer. 
you are powerful. 
you are worth everything you demand and ask for. 
you will not be silenced. & i see you. i love you and i am proud of you. 
_____________________________________________________
long read, but its worth it: i woke up at 7:30 am with a heavy heart and mind. this entire first 7 days of the new year has been reflection and asking god to provide discernment for every encounter i will face. making sure my true vision of where i plan to go aligns with gods purpose for my life. 
i want to forever use my platform as a voice to share my stories in order to inspire change, & thought provoking messages. i am beyond disgusted by the entire #survivingrkelly documentary. thankful for sharing but disgusted it happened and is still happening. 
my heart was beating so fast and tears rolled down my eyes knowing that this man is walking the streets, living his life, and these women have nothing but money & pain to cover a wound. i have so many questions? how, why, what?!? so many questions as tears rolled down my eyes and anger started to ponder. 
the bottom line is that there is culture in the fashion industry and entertainment industry that is sick. yes, not all people in each industry partake in this behavior but the fact that some do is the reason i created @marzenterprise to be a voice for women not spoken for. at age 13, i was raped by a man i didnâ€™t know. i was paralyzed by fear and didnâ€™t have a moment to conclude my way out of the situation. that situation changed my life deeper than i would ever know. i am learning to share this part with women. no matter the circumstances you can heal better, you can still love, you can still grow, and you will still bloom. 
let me reintroduce myself my name is jasmine c. green and thatâ€™s who and all i am. the ceo, and founder of marz management and consulting enterprise, where we eradicate the limitations placed on creatives of color by expanding knowledge on diversity, sexual harassment, as well as health and wellness in the fashion industry. i am a #survivor. do not be afraid, no man can hurt what god deemed as powerful.
#metoo

text: r. kelly is doing some major damage control that may be too little, too late. a new documentary called â€œsurviving r kellyâ€ is burning up the airwaves and the internet alike. the 6 part documentary goes deep into long time allegations that the artist who calls himself the â€œpied piper of r&bâ€ after a fairytale character who used a flute to hypnotize over 130 children away from their parents never to be seen again as an act of revenge.  there are millions of r kellyâ€™s fans and several celebrities who have turned on the singer since the documentary aired including john legend, chance the rapper, roots drummer quest love and others.  some people even believe the singerâ€™s arrogance after being acquitted on several sexual abuse charges was out of control since it seems that his song lyrics seem to taunt authorities and parents alike, some of whom havenâ€™t seen their children in years and believed to be held captive as sex slaves for the singer.  itâ€™s hard to believe that r kelly will escape his fate this time as the #metoo movement is in full swing and determined to make abusers answer for their crimes.  #metoo #rkelly #survivingrkelly #lifetime

text:
i wanted to start the new year on a positive note. but there is so much stupidity in this world, and sometimes this stupidity needs to be shared for others to take note, and think before they speak.

@moixyann a french writer/director/presenter, not a man of extra ordinary beauty himself, thought it okay in the post #metoo era, to age shame women, by telling marie claire fr in an interview, that he would never be able to love a 50 year old woman, being 50 himself. that idea would never come to mind. to moix, 50 year old women are invisible. he finds the 25 year old female body extra ordinary, contrary to a 50 year old female body. when he's 60 he could. because then he would think of a 50 year old woman as young. 
dear mr @moixyann, 
we, almost 50 and 50+ women, could never love stupid men like you, who still think of women as a piece of meat in the year 2019. apparently you didn't notice that we're years and years beyond the stone age, and we therefore advise men like you, to get in touch with doc. brown who can send you back to the future. 
yours sincerely,

text:
if a friend or family member is in an abusive relationship, be aware that they may have a very different point of view than you. they may have heard the abuse was their fault and feel responsible. even if they know it is an abusive relationship, they may choose to stay in the relationship. as a loved one, try to be there for them because although they may not show it, they need you more than ever. one way you can help is to acknowledge that they are in a very difficult and scary situation. be supportive and listen. let them know that the abuse is not their fault. reassure them that they are not alone and that there is help and support out there. it may be difficult for them to talk about the abuse. let them know that you are available to help whenever they may need it. what they need most is someone who will believe and listen.

if you have other questions about what you can do to help or just need support for yourself call us anytime, day or night, at 1-844-be-safe-1.

text:
it's a mixed bag of gratitude when "justice" occurs where "justice" was never served to begin with. i don't understand how she was sentenced in this way but can only hope that the clemency of cyntoia brown will challenge current cases and prevent similar outcomes in the future. 
this is why #ibelieveher and #blacklivesmatter. this is why the #metoo
movement matters (which, btw, originated by @taranajaneen pre hashtag world as an advocacy for black women survivors of sexual assault and violence. check out her organization just be inc.). also to note, look up the stats on abuse and violence against women of color. if that doesn't get you to care about this, then maybe it's time to get your heart checked. 
there are so many systemic issues and failures where our system protects a majority (that often is family, friends, and supporters of the system makers) but majorly fails the minorities and the marginalized. this post isn't an answer, because the answers start with you and what you are doing to be the change in the world. this is just a little psa.

text:
orthorexiaÂ is the term for a condition that includes symptoms of obsessive behavior in pursuit of a healthy diet. orthorexia sufferers often display signs and symptoms of anxiety disorders that frequently co-occur withÂ anorexia nervosaÂ or otherÂ eating disorders.
a person with orthorexia will be obsessed with defining and maintaining the perfect diet, rather than an ideal weight. she will fixate on eating foods that give her a feeling of being pure and healthy. an orthorexic may avoid numerous foods, including those made with:
* artificial colors, flavors or preservatives
* pesticides or genetic modification
* fat, sugar or salt
* animal or dairy products
* other ingredients considered to be unhealthy
common behavior changes that may be signs of orthorexia may include:
* obsessive concern over the relationship between food choices and health concerns such as asthma, digestive problems, low mood, anxiety or allergies
* increasing avoidance of foods because of food allergies, without medical advice
* noticeable increase in consumption of supplements, herbal remedies or probiotics
* drastic reduction in opinions of acceptable food choices, such that the sufferer may eventually consume fewer than 10 foods
* irrational concern over food preparation techniques, especially washing of food or sterilization of utensils
words from @timberlineknolls website ğŸ’›

text: i promised myself that this year i wouldnâ€™t act as if iâ€™m cnn. whilst i have great reason to be outraged at least twenty three hours of the day, i will say iâ€™ve noticed taking in every bit of negative news to be leaving me with headaches and waves of anxiety. but today a pop of paracetamol may be worth it. i havenâ€™t watched the â€˜surviving r.kellyâ€™ documentary. i didnâ€™t need to. sexual assault is so ingrained in the lives of black women, itâ€™s a wonder how itâ€™s not being sold next to tampax. growing up, most all my friends if not for sure their mothers had very violent stories of rape or sexual assault almost always committed by a person considered family. if not rape then for sure all of us has some sexual tryst with a man that knew us before we traded milk for mojitos and shouldâ€™ve known better. during slavery, rape was widely used as a form of discipline. for both men and women. as the years have tumbled forth and some wounds begin to heal, it is clear that we have yet to shake this particular ball and chain. going through comment sections where i read women describing kellyâ€™s victims as â€˜fastâ€™ or â€˜acting too grownâ€™ reminded me of how far we have to go and how important it is to remember that black girls especially are still the bottom of the pile. there is a reason why the founder of the #metoo movement is a black woman. itâ€™s because when it comes to tales of sexual assault black womenâ€™s voices are the last to be heard. but there is hope. i just heard that #cyntoiabrown was granted clemency. found guilty of killing a man who she was forced to sleep with because she was being pimped out at the time. she was 16. sentenced to 51yrs to life, it was clear that the law didnâ€™t see a young black girl who was sexually preyed upon but a threat. like i said, she was just granted full clemency. so perhaps todayâ€™s paracetamol should be prosecco. #blackgirlsmatter

text:
since last year, we've been working on an intersectional guide for survivors on how to deal with #mentalhealth and #wellbeing challenges. if you are in or have been in an abusive relationship, you know what we are talking about. feeling like spinning out of control. feeling low. feeling anxious. triggers. panic attacks. unexplainable feelings. feeling lost and alone. many of us have been through it. 
so this is why we need your help in seeing if our new guide would have been useful when you felt like that or feels useful now? you do not need to be a therapist or psychologist but if you are, please help us too! we will keep comments open until saturday, 12 january. click on the link in our bio to add your feedback! irrespective of whether you help us make this better or not, we just want to say we see you. we hear you. we are with you. you matter. your feelings matter. 
_

text: i know iâ€™m okay, i just need to breathe. breathe past my anxiety, the tears whelping up in my eyes, and all the sadness. most of all, breathe through this completely unexplainable pain in my heart. why canâ€™t i explain why iâ€™m hurt? why can i be so sensitive at the smallest details. it is estimated that 1 out of 5 adults in the us experience some type of mental illness. thatâ€™s around 50 million people that struggle everyday just like you and me. and i believe those who suffer are the strongest souls of them all. those with mental disorders that pick themselves up each day and live their life with true happiness and fulfillment is strong. you are carrying extra weight that others may not and still push no matter the hurtles. how strong are those who are challenged by their own mind each day and still choose to carry on. i donâ€™t like to look weak. i used to hold myself up everyday to hide the fact i felt broken. ashamed of my diagnosis and how others will view me. it took time for me to come to a place where i was okay with being exactly who i am. i took medication, went to therapy, stayed at a hospital. it did help going through all that but what made me love and understand myself was educating myself in my disabilities and learning how they affect me. every day is a challenge but nothing i cannot handle on my own. #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #anxietyrecovery #depression #metoo #overcomedepression #loveyourself

text:
new podcast episode - one of the best ones yet!! trigger warning:
men face different hurdles in the entrepreneurial world. because of today's political correct environment, a lot of times, it's not okay to talk about those hurdles.
this week, purdeep and nathan discuss:
- why it's okay to focus on male entrepreneurs
- the differences between men and women in the workplace
- why the balance of masculine and feminine roles is so important
- how the #metoo movement is actually harming women in the workplace
- what men need to know about the fears women have
- why women can get away with things that men can't
- why women should listen to this podcast
tune in, but be warned. this one is not for the easily offended.
